UNLOAD
  Move a commodity from a ship back into a harbor sector.

SYNTAX
  unload <commodity> <ship-spec> <amount>
  unlo   <commodity> <ship-spec> <amount>

DESCRIPTION
  Transfers goods from a ship's hold into the harbor sector where
  the ship is currently docked.  The ship must be in a harbor
  sector (type 'h') that you own, at least 2% efficient.

  <commodity>  - single letter: f=food c=civ m=mil l=lcm etc.
  <ship-spec>  - ship uid, range (0-5), or * for all ships in harbor
  <amount>     - how many units to unload

  If the ship has fewer than <amount>, it unloads what it has.

EXAMPLE
  unload food 0 200         take 200 food off ship 0
  unload civ 1 50           disembark 50 civilians from ship 1
  unload oil * 100          unload up to 100 oil from every ship

